<Base title="About" prose>
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>
    I'm Trent Jones — a senior full-stack software engineer with 11 years in the industry, the last
    7 at Amazon. At Amazon I've worked on Alexa, across both the mobile and web surfaces.
  </p>
  <p>
    Before Amazon I was at <a href="https://www.fulgentgenetics.com/">Fulgent Genetics</a>, a
    clinical genetics lab, where I worked on the LIMS (lab information management software), clinical
    genomics variant curation and reporting, and the patient-facing web portal.
  </p>
  <p>
    I studied at USC, where I earned dual degrees in <strong>neuroscience</strong> and
    <strong>computer science</strong>. The biology didn't stay in the background — I'm drawn to the
    seam between software and the life sciences, and some of what I build lives there (see
    <a href="/bamcp/">BAMCP</a>, which puts genomic evidence in front of an AI agent).
  </p>
  <p>
    I build self-verifying infrastructure — resilient systems, agentic workflows, and tools that
    prove they work in production rather than asserting it. This site is where I keep them, and it's
    itself one: a thin <a href="https://github.com/RTrentJones/greenlight">Greenlight</a> consumer,
    deployed to Cloudflare Workers and gated by the same verify harness as everything else.
  </p>
  <p>
    Find me on <a href="https://github.com/RTrentJones">GitHub</a> and
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/rtrentjones">LinkedIn</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
